# .cursorrules for My Tailor & Fabrics TBMS

Always Include These Rules in interactions:
1. All money is stored as INTEGER PAISAS. Rs 1,500 = 150000. Never use floats for money.
2. Soft deletes only. All queries must filter: deletedAt IS NULL. Never hard delete.
3. All queries must scope by branchId unless the user role is SUPER_ADMIN.
4. Price snapshot: copy unitPrice + employeeRate onto OrderItem at creation time.
5. EMPLOYEE role must never see unitPrice (customer price) — only their employeeRate.
6. Cancelled items never count toward employee earnings. Enforced at DB query level.
7. TypeScript strict mode. No 'any' types anywhere.
8. All monetary display uses the formatPKR() utility function.
